org.bytedeco.tensorrt.nvinfer

Class IPluginRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bytedeco.javacpp.Pointer
      • org.bytedeco.tensorrt.nvinfer.IPluginRegistry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable

    @Namespace(value="nvinfer1")
 @Properties(inherit=nvinfer.class)
public class IPluginRegistry
extends Pointer
    \class IPluginRegistry \brief Single registration point for all plugins in an application. It is used to find plugin implementations during engine deserialization. Internally, the plugin registry is considered to be a singleton so all plugins in an application are part of the same global registry. Note that the plugin registry is only supported for plugins of type IPluginV2 and should also have a corresponding IPluginCreator implementation.
    See Also:
    and IPluginCreator \warning Do not inherit from this class, as doing so will break forward-compatibility of the API and ABI. \warning In the automotive safety context, be sure to call IPluginRegistry::setErrorRecorder() to register an error recorder with the registry before using other methods in the registry.

      • setErrorRecorder

        @NoException(value=true)
public void setErrorRecorder(IErrorRecorder recorder)
        \brief Set the ErrorRecorder for this interface Assigns the ErrorRecorder to this interface. The ErrorRecorder will track all errors during execution. This function will call incRefCount of the registered ErrorRecorder at least once. Setting recorder to nullptr unregisters the recorder with the interface, resulting in a call to decRefCount if a recorder has been registered.
        Parameters:
        recorder - The error recorder to register with this interface.
        See Also:
        \usage - Allowed context for the API call - Thread-safe: No

        Returns:

      • getAllCreatorsRecursive

        @Cast(value="nvinfer1::IPluginCreatorInterface*const*")
 @NoException(value=true)
public PointerPointer getAllCreatorsRecursive(IntPointer numCreators)
        \brief Return all registered plugin creators by searching starting from the current registry and following parent registries recursively as long as isParentSearchEnabled() returns true.
        Parameters:
        numCreators - [out] Pointer to an integer where the number of registered plugin creators will be stored.
        Returns:
        A pointer to an array of IPluginCreatorInterface pointers. Returns nullptr if no creators are found. \warning If any plugin creators are registered or deregistered after calling this function, the returned pointer is not guaranteed to remain valid. \usage - Allowed context for the API call - Thread-safe: No
